quotas.name: Chhattisgarh Private Seats - Govt Quota
quotas.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Chhattisgarh Private Seats - Govt Quota**

Resident of Chhattisgarh and has passed XII in a Chhattisgarh school.   
Resisdent is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A AND ALSO any one of Criteria B

**Criteria A**

1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or)
2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or)
3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or)
4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years.

**Criteria B**

1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh

**Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)**

1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH
2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this
3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh
4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children

----

If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents

---

Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or) 3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or) 4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years. **Criteria B** 1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh **Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)** 1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH 2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this 3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh 4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children ---- If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents ---
quota.tooltip_content_html:
Eligibility for the Quota : Chhattisgarh Govt Seats


Resident of Chhattisgarh and has passed XII in a Chhattisgarh school.
Resident is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A AND ALSO any one of Criteria B


Criteria A


  1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or)

  2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or)

  3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or)

  4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years.


Criteria B


  1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh


Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)


  1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH

  2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this

  3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh

  4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children


If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents

quota.tooltip_content: **Eligibility for the Quota : Chhattisgarh Govt Seats** Resident of Chhattisgarh and has passed XII in a Chhattisgarh school. Resident is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A **AND ALSO** any one of Criteria B **Criteria A** 1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or) 2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or) 3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or) 4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years. **Criteria B** 1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh **Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)** 1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH 2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this 3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh 4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children ---- If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents ---
quota.tooltip_content_html:
Eligibility for the Quota : Chhattisgarh Govt Seats


Resident of Chhattisgarh and has passed XII in a Chhattisgarh school.
Resident is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A AND ALSO any one of Criteria B


Criteria A


  1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or)

  2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or)

  3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or)

  4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years.


Criteria B


  1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh


Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)


  1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH

  2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this

  3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh

  4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children


If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents

quota.name: Chhattisgarh Private Seats - Govt Quota
quota.tooltip_content:
**Eligibility for the Quota : Chhattisgarh Private Seats - Govt Quota**

Resident of Chhattisgarh and has passed XII in a Chhattisgarh school.   
Resisdent is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A AND ALSO any one of Criteria B

**Criteria A**

1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or)
2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or)
3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or)
4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years.

**Criteria B**

1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh

**Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)**

1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH
2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this
3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh
4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children

----

If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents

---

quota.tooltip_content: **Eligibility for the Quota : Chhattisgarh Govt Seats** Resident of Chhattisgarh and has passed XII in a Chhattisgarh school. Resident is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A **AND ALSO** any one of Criteria B **Criteria A** 1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or) 2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or) 3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or) 4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years. **Criteria B** 1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh **Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)** 1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH 2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this 3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh 4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children ---- If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents ---
quota.tooltip_content_html:
Eligibility for the Quota : Chhattisgarh Govt Seats


Resident of Chhattisgarh and has passed XII in a Chhattisgarh school.
Resident is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A AND ALSO any one of Criteria B


Criteria A


  1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or)

  2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or)

  3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or)

  4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years.


Criteria B


  1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh


Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)


  1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH

  2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this

  3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh

  4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children


If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents

Resident is only if someone satisfies any one of Criteria A AND ALSO any one of Criteria B


Criteria A


  1. Born in Chhattisgarh (or)

  2. Candidate or anyone of the parents or guardian (if parents are not alive) have been living in Chhattisgarh continuously for at least 15 years (or)

  3. Children of those who are serving or retired employee of State Govt or working in Central Govt in Chhattisgarh (or)

  4. He or his parents own any immovable property, business or industry in Chhattisgarh for at least 5 years.


Criteria B


  1. Eight class examination should have been passed from Chhattisgarh


Beyond these the following also become residents (directly)


  1. Spouses or Children of AI officers in CHTSGH

  2. Wife/husband or children of officers/employees of CHTSGH Govt - - query on diff between 3) above and this

  3. Spouses or children of those appointed by the President to statutory posts in Chhattisgarh

  4. Officials/officers/employees posted in institutions or corporations or boards or commissions under State of Chhattisgarh, their wives/husbands or children


If anyone is a resident as per above criteria, their spouses/children, also become bonafide residents
